<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Ghana </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Soldiers Missing in Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Denies Soldiers Missing in Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB0804182194 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in English 1800 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB0804182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Ministry of Defense has denied reports that 
two Ghanaian soldiers serving with the UN Assistance Mission in 
Rwanda are missing. The reports say two Ghanaians and two 
Belgian observers could not be found. A statement issued in 
Accra today and signed by the director of the Public Relations 
Directorate of the Ghana Armed Forces, Colonel Akowia, said the 
commander of the Ghanaian contingent in the mission area has 
confirmed that no Ghanaian officer or man is missing. He added 
that they are all safe and sound. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

